    "# 10. The Dual-Cycling Quay Crane Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tier 4 — The AI/ML/RL Augmentation Method (Imitation Learning Framework)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Goal\n",
    "Implement an Imitation Learning framework that learns optimal dual-cycling crane operation policies from expert demonstrations, combining behavioral cloning with inverse reinforcement learning to capture tacit operational knowledge.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Assumptions\n",
    "- Expert crane operators possess nuanced knowledge about efficient dual-cycling patterns\n",
    "- Historical expert decisions are available for training (simulated dataset)\n",
    "- State representation can capture comprehensive operational context\n",
    "- Action space includes discrete operation types and continuous parameters\n",
    "- Reward function can be discovered through inverse reinforcement learning\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (Step-by-Step)\n",
    "1. **State Feature Extraction**: Comprehensive representation of crane, container, and terminal state\n",
    "2. **Expert Action Encoding**: Multi-dimensional action representation including operation types and parameters\n",
    "3. **Behavioral Cloning**: Supervised learning to directly imitate expert decisions\n",
    "4. **Inverse Reinforcement Learning**: Discover underlying reward structure driving expert behavior\n",
    "5. **Policy Integration**: Combine BC and IRL for robust policy learning\n",
    "6. **Performance Evaluation**: Compare learned policy with expert and baseline performance\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to Look for in the Results\n",
    "- Action prediction accuracy on expert demonstrations\n",
    "- Dual-cycling efficiency of learned policy vs expert performance\n",
    "- Generalization to unseen vessel configurations\n",
    "- Real-time decision making capability (12ms target)\n",
    "- Makespan improvement over rule-based systems"
   ]
  },
